function count_model_rows(df_cars::DataFrame)
    return combine(groupby(df_cars, :model), nrow => :Counts)
end
```

This function uses the `combine` and `groupby` functions from the DataFrames.jl package to group the data by the `:model` column and then calculate the number of rows for each group. The resulting DataFrame will have an additional column called `Counts` that contains the row counts for each model.
